The National Emergency Management Agency (NEMA) said that 11 more bodies of the victims of the ill-fated boat, sailing from Mile-2  to Ibeshe,  have been recovered. A statement from the Spokesman of the agency, Mr. Ibrahim Farinloye said the 11 bodies has made the raised the number of total recovery from the accident to 15, adding that efforts are still on to ensure more recovery. Farinloye accused  boat operators of carrying out services above the official hours 7pm allowed for boat operation by the Inland Waterway..He said that, “the regulatory bodies have tried to stamped out illegal operations of small boat operators who hardly use life jackets after official hours but they do not heed to efforts put in place to stop them “It was also observed that wooding boat are not permitted to be used as passengers boat but its only at this odd hours that the illegal operators’ always put the lives of unsuspecting passengers at risk. “Efforts are on to address the gaps with all stakeholders such as Nigerian Navy’s Special Boat Service , Association of Boat/Ferry Operators of Nigeria, LASWA, NIWA, NEMA and Marine Police to address the situation.”